ffAuthorList":{"14102202337":true}},"1861":{"revisionId":1861,"timestamp":1656193932427,"state":"saved","type":"session","diffAuthorList":{"14102202337":true}}},"lastEditTimestamp":1656261739473,"diffChangeset":"Z:1sv>f|1r=1sp*4|f+f$\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","invalidDiffChangeset":false,"authorList":{"14102202337":{"authorName":"Alina Gafanova","authorCustomAvatarUrl":"/users/14102202337/avatar","lastAccessTime":1656191824325}},"diffAuthorList":{"14102202337":true},"shouldCreateSavepointBeforeApplyingNextRevision":false,"firstKeyRevision":5,"atext":{"text":"0. The data we already have: \n\nColombia, Chile - only adm1\nIndia, Vietnam, Indonesia - adm2\n\nAffected by disasters:\nEarthquakes: India, Indonesia, Chile, Colombia\nCyclones: Vietnam, India\nWe definitely need more countries for cyclones! (Japan, Mexico, US, Philippines,..)\n\n1. Main analysis (lagged regressions on year-firm level):\n\ndifferent approaches for accommodating temporal structure:\n- default: distributed lag model with a fixed number of lags (5/10)\n- local projections (Jorda 2005)\n\nexploiting firms' heterogeneity:\n- firm size\n- firm industry (based on how vulnerable the industry is)\n- SR repeated exposure to a natural disaster (how often that firm/region was exposed in the past few years)\n- LR repeated exposure to a natural disaster (how often that region experiences natural disasters)\n- how capital intensive the firm is\n- etc\n\nusing different exposure variables:\n- default (weighted by area in all the region, dropping non-populated areas)\n- weighted by population\n- only populated area vs all area\n- only top X% of area most affected by disasters\n- number of events vs maximum intensity that year\n\n2. Additional types of analysis we can perform:\n\nFirms exits and entries:\n- comparing raw stats: how different are firms that stay and exit one year before the disaster\n- types of firms entering after the disasters\n- decomposition of productivity: entry vs exit vs reallocation\n\nExploring aggregated effects: running regressions on region-year level instead of firm-level\n\nAdding non-linearity\n\nRereating firms' networks to study spillovers (Couttenier 2022)\n\nDifferent adaptation strategies:\n- location switching (checking aggregated data - If there are switches between adm2 regions)\n- reallocation between sectors (aggregated data - on sector-region level)\n- reallocation within firms ( investment in new technologies? new products?)\n\nSearching for policies with different temporal roll-out related to aid after disasters\nNew insurance policies or something along the lines\n\n\n\nI have created a list of variables\nVariables that are in most datasets: start year of operation, industry, employment, sales, capital, inventories, wages and labor costs, VA, cost of inputs (probably not perfectly harmonizable), exports (often exist for limited number of firms)\n\n\n\n\nparagraph summary of all the results in words\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","attribs":"*4*9*5*6+t*4|2+2*4*5*6+r*4|1+1*4*5*6+w*4|2+2*4*5*6+m*4|1+1*4*5*6+1a*4|1+1*4*5*6+o*4|1+1*4*5*6+2b*4|2+2*4*9*5*6+2*4*9+1*4*9*5*6+1i*4|2+2*4*5*6+1m*4|1+1*4*5*6+1v*4|1+1*4*5*6+w*4|2+2*4*5*6+w*4|1+1*4*5*6+b*4|1+1*4*5*6+1l*4|1+1*4*5*6+2z*4|1+1*4*5*6+2q*4|1+1*4*5*6+z*4|1+1*4*5*6+5*4|2+2*4*5*6+z*4|1+1*4*5*6+24*4|1+1*4*5*6+2*4*6+m*4|1+1*4*5*6+x*4|1+1*4*5*6+1c*4|1+1*4*5*6+1d*4|2+2*4*9*5*6+1b*4|2+2*4*5*6+o*4|1+1*4*5*6+2m*4|1+1*4*5*6+19*4|1+1*4*5*6+2*4*6+t*4*5*6+2*4*6+t*4|2+2*4*5*6+2k*4|2+2*4*5*6+k*4|2+2*4*5*6+1r*4|2+2*4*5*6+w*4|1+1*4*5*6+2k*4|1+1*4*5*6+21*4|1+1*4*5*6+24*4|2+2*4+a*4*5*6+4*4|1+21*4*5*6+1f*4|4+4*4*5*6+y*4|1+1*4*5*6+6r*4|1+1*4*a|1+1*4|2+2*4*a|1+1*4*9*5*a+19*4*a|1+1*4|m+m|1+1","opCount":94,"appliedAttribsCount":191,"maxAttribsOnSingleOp":4},"pool":{"numToAttrib":{"0":["author","a.4fz9s4pIrvcRKF5l"],"1":["align","left"],"2":["insertorder","first"],"3":["lmkr","1"],"4":["author","14102202337"],"5":["font-color-000000","true"],"6":["font-size-medium","true"],"7":["remove